utation of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1244, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wasteful over-spending\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"construction work\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"extravagant \\\"white elephant\\\" infrastructure projects\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1184}, {\"ngram\": \"the reputation\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Concerns about climate change have also led activists to target the enormous carbon footprint of an event that brings together athletes and spectators from across the world every four years.\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1436, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Concerns\", \"from\": 1246, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"activists\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"the enormous carbon footprint\", \"from\": 1310, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1418}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris organisers see themselves as promoting a new \\\"sober\\\" model, with a focus on using existing or temporary sporting infrastructure, as well as promoting recycling, re-use and innovative low-carbon technologies.\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1438, \"end\": 1443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999997726, \"rank\": 3.0057217933871766e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a new \\\"sober\\\" model\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1516}, {\"ngram\": \"existing or temporary